1536718604209029125.Text: There is a rumor in Vivec that Miun-Gei, a merchant in the Vivec Foreign Quarter, has been having problems with an annoying street vendor selling things outside his shop.

10105276041841317279.Text: I've spoken to Miun-Gei about the person outside his shop disrupting business. He claims the man is hawking ridiculous items, and generally annoying his customers. Since he technically isn't doing anything illegal, there is no way to get rid of him, but Miun-Gei would like him gone.

16600623887323500.Text: I've agreed to help Miun-Gei get rid of the annoying vendor, whose name is Marcel Maurard.

5169298942611819916.Text: I've decided not to deal with the actor bothering Miun-Gei.

26556218931096329664.Text: After speaking to Marcel Maurard, I've found that he is an aspiring actor, who is trying to make money to fund his craft. He refuses to leave, since it is the only way he has found to make any cash, at least until he can find a part in a play.

21692286391588814175.Text: After asking around a bit in Vivec, I've learned that there is almost no actual theatre here in the city. In fact, the only one who is interested at all is Crassius Curio, a nobleman in town.

20651132521726118577.Text: Crassius Curio is putting on a new play called "The Lusty Argonian Maid," and gave me a bit of the work to sample.

1960022600150344984.Text: I have spoken to Crassius Curio, and it seems he is very interested in the arts, especially the theatre. He would like to stage a production of his latest play, but hasn't been able to find enough actors willing to take part.

3699284432838613332.Text: Marcel Maurard was overjoyed to hear about Curio's play. He promised he would visit him as soon as possible and join with the acting troupe.

4594009647231374.Text: Miun-Gei was happy to hear that Marcel Maurard will no longer be selling his wares in front of his shop, and rewarded me with an iron shardskewer.

148783116026451344.Text: I've killed Marcel Maurard, and Miun-Gei is glad he's gone. He's not happy that the guards will be around asking questions, though. He rewarded me with 250 gold.
